15
00:02:12,350 --> 00:02:13,050
There's one more.

16
00:02:23,670 --> 00:02:24,610
He'll be happy

17
00:02:24,720 --> 00:02:26,020
to know that.

18
00:02:30,620 --> 00:02:34,460
[To Su Yun:
Sincerely invite you to join my team]

19
00:02:49,600 --> 00:02:50,260
Come on in.

20
00:02:57,440 --> 00:02:58,050
What?

21
00:02:58,230 --> 00:02:58,980
Want to share my meal?

22
00:03:13,620 --> 00:03:17,460
[To Su Yun:
Sincerely invite you to join my team]

23
00:03:20,200 --> 00:03:21,140
Do...

24
00:03:22,670 --> 00:03:23,330
Do you want it?

25
00:03:26,920 --> 00:03:29,260
Want what? Be specific.

26
00:03:33,950 --> 00:03:34,980
You can read it

27
00:03:35,280 --> 00:03:36,210
if you find it difficult.

28
00:03:41,280 --> 00:03:42,890
I know you can't hold a scalpel yet,

29
00:03:45,510 --> 00:03:47,100
that you're not ready,

30
00:03:48,230 --> 00:03:49,580
and that it's insulting for you

31
00:03:50,350 --> 00:03:51,650
to be an assistant,

32
00:03:53,510 --> 00:03:54,490
but I also know

33
00:03:55,440 --> 00:03:56,180
that you want more than anyone else

34
00:03:56,180 --> 00:03:57,450
for this surgery to be successful

35
00:03:58,600 --> 00:04:00,300
and for the Siamese twins

36
00:04:01,720 --> 00:04:03,420
to live to have a normal life.

37
00:04:05,790 --> 00:04:07,450
This is a very difficult surgery

38
00:04:07,950 --> 00:04:08,880
and may take more than
20 healthcare professionals

39
00:04:08,880 --> 00:04:09,930
working together

40
00:04:09,950 --> 00:04:11,540
to accomplish.

41
00:04:12,920 --> 00:04:13,490
The chief surgeon,

42
00:04:14,230 --> 00:04:14,860
the assistants,

43
00:04:15,480 --> 00:04:16,410
the nurses, and the anesthesiologist.

44
00:04:17,430 --> 00:04:19,020
They're all an integral part.

45
00:04:19,640 --> 00:04:20,410
To me,

46
00:04:22,080 --> 00:04:23,450
you were a very good companion.

47
00:04:25,990 --> 00:04:26,650
In the beginning,

48
00:04:27,430 --> 00:04:29,290
you took me into this surgery,

49
00:04:30,400 --> 00:04:31,020
so now,

50
00:04:32,040 --> 00:04:33,140
I'm going to take you in.

51
00:04:34,480 --> 00:04:35,330
We'll do it together.

52
00:04:56,480 --> 00:04:57,140
Okay.

53
00:04:58,230 --> 00:04:59,180
For the sake

54
00:04:59,960 --> 00:05:01,090
of your sincerity.

55
00:05:02,160 --> 00:05:03,020
Is that a yes?

56
00:05:03,550 --> 00:05:04,330
How could I not say yes?

57
00:05:04,350 --> 00:05:05,180
I'm like this now,

58
00:05:05,600 --> 00:05:06,940
so I have to.

59
00:05:07,550 --> 00:05:08,290
Then let's get to work.

60
00:05:11,790 --> 00:05:12,450
What?

61
00:05:12,750 --> 00:05:13,770
Another surprise?

62
00:05:15,060 --> 00:05:17,260
[To He Qian:
Sincerely invite you to join my team]

63
00:05:17,640 --> 00:05:19,210
Zheng Ren, can't you be kind?

64
00:05:19,350 --> 00:05:20,850
I need to run errands now?

65
00:05:21,280 --> 00:05:22,620
What a jerk.

66
00:05:24,400 --> 00:05:26,150
But you're already on my team.

67
00:05:26,150 --> 00:05:27,620
Your team?

68
00:05:34,700 --> 00:05:37,420
[Episode 18] [Intrauterine
Intervention Surgery - Parents]

69
00:05:39,230 --> 00:05:40,580
Dr. Zheng is amazing.

70
00:05:40,580 --> 00:05:41,960
It's a different world

71
00:05:41,960 --> 00:05:43,090
after he came back from Beida.

72
00:05:43,960 --> 00:05:45,350
I heard Beida wanted him,

73
00:05:45,350 --> 00:05:46,330
but he didn't agree.

74
00:05:46,750 --> 00:05:47,580
Of course.

75
00:05:47,720 --> 00:05:48,820
We have to keep a talent

76
00:05:48,820 --> 00:05:49,820
like him in our hospital.

77
00:05:50,720 --> 00:05:52,060
Who's on his team?

78
00:05:52,280 --> 00:05:53,120
Yun.

79
00:05:53,120 --> 00:05:53,830
Yun?

80
00:05:54,790 --> 00:05:55,970
He can hold a scalpel?

81
00:05:56,080 --> 00:05:57,260
He's a medical assistant.

82
00:05:57,350 --> 00:05:58,180
What?

83
00:05:58,720 --> 00:05:59,650
Surprised, right?

84
00:05:59,750 --> 00:06:00,500
Me too.

85
00:06:00,720 --> 00:06:01,400
Before,

86
00:06:01,400 --> 00:06:02,740
I wouldn't have believed

87
00:06:02,740 --> 00:06:03,740
he'd be an assistant anyway.

88
00:06:03,920 --> 00:06:05,260
In hindsight,

89
00:06:05,350 --> 00:06:06,960
Dr. Zheng was so amazing

90
00:06:06,960 --> 00:06:08,850
that he convinced Yun.

91
00:06:09,870 --> 00:06:10,530
Yiren.

92
00:06:11,840 --> 00:06:13,940
Didn't you go to Beida this time?

93
00:06:14,480 --> 00:06:15,700
Tell us.

94
00:06:16,110 --> 00:06:17,020
How did these two

95
00:06:17,020 --> 00:06:18,020
turn into friends?

96
00:06:18,020 --> 00:06:18,940
I don't know.

97
00:06:19,920 --> 00:06:22,260
Maybe it's a genius sympathy.

98
00:06:22,720 --> 00:06:23,850
Genius sympathy?

99
00:06:23,850 --> 00:06:24,970
Genius sympathy?

100
00:06:26,190 --> 00:06:28,180
What are the requirements

101
00:06:28,180 --> 00:06:29,210
for Zheng Ren's team?

102
00:06:29,350 --> 00:06:30,770
I also want to join.

103
00:06:30,770 --> 00:06:31,740
Don't even think about it.

104
00:06:31,870 --> 00:06:33,620
They want doctors.

105
00:06:34,280 --> 00:06:35,410
Nothing to do with nurses.

106
00:06:36,750 --> 00:06:37,890
There's no hope.

107
00:06:48,740 --> 00:06:51,820
[Office Building]

108
00:06:53,750 --> 00:06:54,660
Please come in.

109
00:06:57,480 --> 00:06:58,290
Come on, He.

110
00:07:00,150 --> 00:07:00,730
Ms. Su.

111
00:07:00,950 --> 00:07:02,170
Yun, Zheng.

112
00:07:02,800 --> 00:07:03,900
How was your trip

113
00:07:04,070 --> 00:07:05,050
to Beida?

114
00:07:05,190 --> 00:07:06,610
Exciting.

115
00:07:06,920 --> 00:07:07,730
We beat those masters.

116
00:07:07,750 --> 00:07:08,490
What a humiliation for them.

117
00:07:08,560 --> 00:07:09,410
It was a great comeback.

118
00:07:09,440 --> 00:07:09,930
Exciting.

119
00:07:09,950 --> 00:07:10,700
Isn't it, Yun?

120
00:07:11,560 --> 00:07:12,660
Do you want to join us

121
00:07:13,310 --> 00:07:14,580
for the conjoined twins
separation surgery?

122
00:07:15,630 --> 00:07:16,490
Oh, my God.

123
00:07:17,000 --> 00:07:18,220
Of course, I want to.

124
00:07:19,270 --> 00:07:20,730
If Zheng and Yun were interested in me,

125
00:07:21,000 --> 00:07:22,490
I'd be more than willing.

126
00:07:23,040 --> 00:07:23,780
But there's something

127
00:07:23,780 --> 00:07:24,700
I have to explain to you.

128
00:07:24,750 --> 00:07:25,850
What is that?

129
00:07:26,310 --> 00:07:27,290
In the anesthesia department,

130
00:07:27,310 --> 00:07:28,290
you currently have a base salary,

131
00:07:28,440 --> 00:07:29,370
surgical allowance,

132
00:07:29,480 --> 00:07:30,460
overtime pay, and all that,

133
00:07:31,190 --> 00:07:31,900
but if you...

134
00:07:31,900 --> 00:07:32,540
But,

135
00:07:32,600 --> 00:07:33,980
when I join the team,

136
00:07:34,800 --> 00:07:35,780
all that goes away?

137
00:07:37,600 --> 00:07:38,540
It's a hospital rule.

138
00:07:38,920 --> 00:07:40,660
After all, there's no
actual revenue generation.

139
00:07:40,800 --> 00:07:41,930
In the meantime,

140
00:07:42,120 --> 00:07:43,810
all research expenses

141
00:07:44,310 --> 00:07:45,730
are met by the team itself.

142
00:07:52,390 --> 00:07:53,340
This means

143
00:07:53,950 --> 00:07:55,390
that when I join the team,

144
00:07:55,480 --> 00:07:57,220
the old surgeries are gone

145
00:07:57,480 --> 00:07:58,850
and the new ones

146
00:07:58,880 --> 00:08:00,610
may not last as long.

147
00:08:00,800 --> 00:08:01,490
Yes.

148
00:08:02,880 --> 00:08:03,490
Of course,

149
00:08:04,440 --> 00:08:06,110
if the team itself attracts

150
00:08:06,110 --> 00:08:07,220
outside investment,

151
00:08:07,710 --> 00:08:09,140
we will not interfere

152
00:08:09,140 --> 00:08:10,540
with subsidizing the members.

153
00:08:14,360 --> 00:08:15,100
Mr. Zheng,

154
00:08:15,800 --> 00:08:17,100
is the surgery a sure thing?

155
00:08:18,630 --> 00:08:19,250
No.

156
00:08:19,800 --> 00:08:21,100
Then you are still doing it?

157
00:08:21,120 --> 00:08:21,660
Of course.

158
00:08:22,440 --> 00:08:23,250
We must.

159
00:08:23,560 --> 00:08:24,600
For the sake of research

160
00:08:24,600 --> 00:08:25,700
and saving lives.

161
00:08:25,830 --> 00:08:27,100
We don't have the money at this stage,

162
00:08:27,150 --> 00:08:28,140
but we don't know about the future.

163
00:08:28,680 --> 00:08:29,290
He.

164
00:08:30,000 --> 00:08:31,050
We've done some budgeting.

165
00:08:31,440 --> 00:08:32,630
The cost of upgrading

166
00:08:32,630 --> 00:08:33,580
the virtual operating room alone

167
00:08:33,790 --> 00:08:35,420
is beyond the means
of the patient's family.

168
00:08:44,550 --> 00:08:45,250
Ms. Su.

169
00:08:45,390 --> 00:08:45,940
Yun.

170
00:08:46,150 --> 00:08:46,940
Zheng.

171
00:08:47,510 --> 00:08:48,650
I don't want to join.

172
00:08:48,750 --> 00:08:49,420
Thank you.

173
00:08:55,000 --> 00:08:56,010
Am I right?

174
00:08:56,270 --> 00:08:57,370
He's not going to join.

175
00:08:57,510 --> 00:08:58,580
He's the most cash-strapped

176
00:08:58,750 --> 00:08:59,770
out of all people at the hospital.

177
00:08:59,960 --> 00:09:01,250
But I checked his file.

178
00:09:02,120 --> 00:09:03,770
He's been in clinical anesthesia
for 15 years.

179
00:09:04,080 --> 00:09:05,180
He's really good

180
00:09:06,390 --> 00:09:07,610
and shouldn't stop there.

181
00:09:08,200 --> 00:09:09,820
It's cruel to oppress people
who are short of money

182
00:09:10,480 --> 00:09:11,700
with dreams.

183
00:09:33,550 --> 00:09:34,160
Mei.

184
00:09:34,200 --> 00:09:35,220
Dad.

185
00:09:35,720 --> 00:09:36,300
Dad.

186
00:09:36,320 --> 00:09:36,770
Hey, sweetie.

187
00:09:36,790 --> 00:09:38,010
Look at this.

188
00:09:39,430 --> 00:09:40,940
Parasaurolophus.

189
00:09:41,030 --> 00:09:42,730
It's a cymatium that makes sounds.

190
00:09:43,120 --> 00:09:43,700
You were good,

191
00:09:43,700 --> 00:09:44,610
so I'm rewarding you.

192
00:09:45,000 --> 00:09:45,770
Thank you, Daddy.

193
00:09:46,030 --> 00:09:46,700
You're welcome.

194
00:09:47,150 --> 00:09:47,980
Mom.

195
00:09:48,000 --> 00:09:49,580
Daddy's home!

196
00:09:53,960 --> 00:09:55,580
You're finally back.

197
00:09:55,840 --> 00:09:57,420
You've been gone so long

198
00:09:57,840 --> 00:09:59,580
that people think I've lost my husband.

199
00:10:00,360 --> 00:10:02,010
Put this over there.

200
00:10:02,240 --> 00:10:02,850
OK.

201
00:10:09,430 --> 00:10:10,250
Honey.

202
00:10:10,390 --> 00:10:11,980
I have something to discuss
with you later.

203
00:10:12,150 --> 00:10:13,250
Dad!

204
00:10:13,510 --> 00:10:14,980
How do you answer this question?

205
00:10:17,240 --> 00:10:17,840
Which one?

206
00:10:17,840 --> 00:10:18,610
This one.

207
00:10:21,150 --> 00:10:22,980
Transfer 50,000 to me later.

208
00:10:23,670 --> 00:10:24,940
Didn't I just give it to you
at the beginning of the month?

209
00:10:24,940 --> 00:10:25,890
That was for home use.

210
00:10:26,480 --> 00:10:27,940
It's almost November 11th.

211
00:10:28,000 --> 00:10:28,580
Look.

212
00:10:28,630 --> 00:10:30,010
I've stocked up on so many goods.

213
00:10:30,080 --> 00:10:31,180
If I don't spend some money

214
00:10:31,180 --> 00:10:32,700
to do some activities and gifts,

215
00:10:32,720 --> 00:10:33,490
how can I increase my popularity?

216
00:10:33,720 --> 00:10:35,100
Without popularity,
how can I sell my products?

217
00:10:35,270 --> 00:10:36,250
Without selling products,

218
00:10:36,320 --> 00:10:37,300
can I count on you?

219
00:10:38,840 --> 00:10:40,060
Why are you looking at me?

220
00:10:40,720 --> 00:10:42,370
Don't say you don't have money now.

221
00:10:42,370 --> 00:10:43,370
This is not negotiable.

222
00:10:47,270 --> 00:10:48,890
What did you want to tell me?

223
00:10:51,030 --> 00:10:51,730
Nothing.

224
00:11:25,780 --> 00:11:27,260
[Zhang Sheng, Resume]

225
00:11:27,300 --> 00:11:28,980
[Wang Xuekuan, Resume]

226
00:11:29,030 --> 00:11:29,820
Just choose one.

227
00:11:31,910 --> 00:11:33,730
But it's hard
to find an anesthesiologist

228
00:11:33,880 --> 00:11:35,100
who'll put up with your long slavery

229
00:11:35,360 --> 00:11:36,100
without payment.

230
00:11:37,750 --> 00:11:39,300
What if I give He Qian my salary?

231
00:11:40,120 --> 00:11:40,980
Come on.

232
00:11:41,550 --> 00:11:42,700
How much do you think you get paid?

233
00:11:45,120 --> 00:11:45,700
Not enough?

234
00:11:46,080 --> 00:11:46,820
You, as a newcomer,

235
00:11:46,840 --> 00:11:48,130
always pay for the patients,

236
00:11:48,200 --> 00:11:49,250
always give,

237
00:11:49,510 --> 00:11:50,770
are so stingy when doing surgeries

238
00:11:50,790 --> 00:11:52,300
that you use domestics
instead of imports,

239
00:11:52,430 --> 00:11:54,010
and always use your hands
instead of consumables,

240
00:11:54,080 --> 00:11:55,250
so how much do you think
you'll have left in your paycheck?

241
00:11:59,880 --> 00:12:00,650
Hello, Doraemon.

242
00:12:00,910 --> 00:12:01,820
Dr. Zheng, Dr. Su.

243
00:12:02,030 --> 00:12:03,180
Guess what I brought.

244
00:12:05,480 --> 00:12:06,610
Pumpkin pie.

245
00:12:06,720 --> 00:12:07,250
Done.

246
00:12:07,510 --> 00:12:08,060
Yiren.

247
00:12:08,120 --> 00:12:09,460
Haven't you had enough
of his lack of appreciation?

248
00:12:10,430 --> 00:12:11,100
Try it.

249
00:12:18,150 --> 00:12:18,700
How is it?

250
00:12:19,790 --> 00:12:20,980
You didn't spit it out.

251
00:12:21,080 --> 00:12:21,650
Is it good?

252
00:12:22,430 --> 00:12:23,250
I'll try it too.

253
00:12:25,630 --> 00:12:26,420
It's salty?

254
00:12:27,030 --> 00:12:28,700
You put salt and cumin in it?

255
00:12:29,270 --> 00:12:30,610
What a strange flavor.

256
00:12:41,030 --> 00:12:41,650
How is it?

257
00:12:45,360 --> 00:12:45,940
Good.

258
00:12:49,430 --> 00:12:50,610
Hello, Mr. Pan.

259
00:12:51,120 --> 00:12:52,490
How's your recovery going?

260
00:12:52,840 --> 00:12:54,080
I'm doing great.

261
00:12:54,080 --> 00:12:55,180
Is something wrong?

262
00:12:55,390 --> 00:12:56,370
No.

263
00:12:56,430 --> 00:12:58,130
I just care about you.

264
00:12:58,550 --> 00:12:59,730
Stop it.

265
00:12:59,880 --> 00:13:01,180
You think I don't know you?

266
00:13:01,240 --> 00:13:02,890
Tell me. What do you want?

267
00:13:04,910 --> 00:13:05,940
So...

268
00:13:06,120 --> 00:13:07,060
Have you ever eaten the pumpkin pie

269
00:13:07,080 --> 00:13:08,700
made by Zheng Ren's mom?

270
00:13:16,510 --> 00:13:17,650
Dr. Zheng, Dr. Su.

271
00:13:17,750 --> 00:13:19,460
What were you talking about?

272
00:13:20,080 --> 00:13:21,340
He wants to invite He Qian.

273
00:13:21,340 --> 00:13:22,820
But He Qian wouldn't join
because he wouldn't get paid.

274
00:13:24,030 --> 00:13:25,700
Conjoined twins separation surgery.

275
00:13:25,700 --> 00:13:27,580
That would be the first case
in the city.

276
00:13:27,960 --> 00:13:28,890
Rare in the whole country.

277
00:13:29,390 --> 00:13:30,940
But for a surgery like this,

278
00:13:30,960 --> 00:13:32,610
there should be a lot of foundations

279
00:13:32,670 --> 00:13:33,370
and websites

280
00:13:33,430 --> 00:13:34,420
that are willing to sponsor it.

281
00:13:34,510 --> 00:13:35,650
You're talking about Peng Jia, right?

282
00:13:36,270 --> 00:13:37,460
He's too ambitious

283
00:13:37,600 --> 00:13:39,130
and won't sacrifice his own interests.

284
00:13:39,390 --> 00:13:40,060
And,

285
00:13:40,360 --> 00:13:42,320
don't even think
about the live broadcast.

286
00:13:42,670 --> 00:13:44,180
Since I was invited to join the team,

287
00:13:44,240 --> 00:13:45,470
I have to be the gatekeeper
for everything.

288
00:13:45,670 --> 00:13:47,250
This kind of nonsense should go away.

289
00:13:48,200 --> 00:13:48,820
Zheng Ren.

290
00:13:49,750 --> 00:13:50,890
You're all here. Just in time.

291
00:13:51,390 --> 00:13:52,370
Let's take a look at this.

292
00:13:54,080 --> 00:13:54,890
Two months ago,

293
00:13:54,890 --> 00:13:55,820
a gynecological examination

294
00:13:55,880 --> 00:13:57,010
[Ultrasound report]
of a woman

295
00:13:57,030 --> 00:13:57,820
at the age of 39

296
00:13:57,840 --> 00:13:59,070
revealed that the fetus

297
00:13:59,070 --> 00:14:00,140
may have

298
00:14:00,140 --> 00:14:01,130
congenital aortic stenosis.

299
00:14:01,150 --> 00:14:02,100
The fetus was 24 weeks old
at the time.

300
00:14:02,120 --> 00:14:03,220
Fetal congenital aortic stenosis
can be seen

301
00:14:03,240 --> 00:14:04,820
when the fetus
is just twenty-four weeks old.

302
00:14:05,080 --> 00:14:06,320
Which doctor is so amazing?

303
00:14:06,320 --> 00:14:06,980
Dr. Wang.

304
00:14:07,430 --> 00:14:08,580
The old lady who was rehired.

305
00:14:08,630 --> 00:14:09,530
Mr. Pan's classmate.

306
00:14:10,030 --> 00:14:10,980
She's really good.

307
00:14:11,720 --> 00:14:13,130
Dr. Wang suggested inducing labor.

308
00:14:14,390 --> 00:14:15,240
The congenital anomaly

309
00:14:15,240 --> 00:14:16,220
of the aortic valve

310
00:14:16,430 --> 00:14:17,460
leads to progressive dysplasia

311
00:14:17,460 --> 00:14:18,730
and heart failure,

312
00:14:18,880 --> 00:14:19,650
resulting in hypoplastic

313
00:14:19,650 --> 00:14:20,610
left heart syndrome.

314
00:14:20,670 --> 00:14:22,010
Even if the patient gives birth
to the baby alive,

315
00:14:22,430 --> 00:14:23,770
she'll still be in a lot of trouble.

316
00:14:24,720 --> 00:14:26,530
But the pregnant woman
refused to be induced

317
00:14:26,670 --> 00:14:27,700
and expected a miracle.

318
00:14:27,750 --> 00:14:28,390
And then?

319
00:14:28,390 --> 00:14:29,460
When she came
for an obstetric examination just now,

320
00:14:29,550 --> 00:14:30,370
Dr. Wang found

321
00:14:30,390 --> 00:14:31,700
that the condition
of the fetus was deteriorating.

322
00:14:31,720 --> 00:14:33,340
The ratio of the left and right ventricles
is gradually abnormal.

323
00:14:33,430 --> 00:14:34,370
Fetal pericardial effusion

324
00:14:34,430 --> 00:14:35,610
and mitral regurgitation

325
00:14:35,610 --> 00:14:36,530
appear one after another.

326
00:14:37,120 --> 00:14:38,480
The GYN has two other options.

327
00:14:38,480 --> 00:14:38,940
One.

328
00:14:39,120 --> 00:14:40,700
Close observation
and conservative treatment,

329
00:14:40,790 --> 00:14:42,250
but with the current condition
of the fetus,

330
00:14:42,250 --> 00:14:43,610
it will not last for natural delivery.

331
00:14:43,910 --> 00:14:45,180
Two, prepare for cesarean section.

332
00:14:45,430 --> 00:14:46,400
After delivery,

333
00:14:46,400 --> 00:14:47,680
the baby will be taken
to another operating table

334
00:14:47,680 --> 00:14:48,530
to be treated with extracardiac therapy.

335
00:14:49,120 --> 00:14:49,730
Wait a minute.

336
00:14:50,630 --> 00:14:52,140
Pediatric cardiac surgery
should be Chang Yue's job.

337
00:14:52,140 --> 00:14:53,150
